=== Patients Considering Medical Assistance in Dying

    - *Ethical imperative*: Try aggressive symptom management _before_ irreversible decision
    - *2-week trial*: Commit to full protocol for 14 days before final decision
    - *Transformation possible*: 50–70% symptom reduction can change perspective from “unbearable” to “difficult but bearable”
    - *Buying time*: Even if not cured, reducing suffering buys time for new treatments (research advancing rapidly)
    - *Support*: Connect with ME/CFS patient communities; others have been where you are and found ways to continue

